<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="561" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,510,1726]" pageId="12" pageNumber="561">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1593,1618]" pageId="12" pageNumber="561">Remarks</emphasis>
. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang" authorityName="Yang" box="[654,852,1593,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basalis">
<emphasis box="[654,767,1593,1617]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="561">H. basalis</emphasis>
(Yang)
</taxonomicName>
from Xinjiang of 
<collectingCountry box="[1056,1126,1593,1618]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="561">China</collectingCountry>
, but may be separated from the latter by the big, apically-hooked postgonite and long bristles of male cercus. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1101,1215,1629,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basalis">
<emphasis box="[1101,1215,1629,1653]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="561">H. basalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the postgonite and the bristles of male cercus are relatively short (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang" box="[674,816,1665,1690]" pageId="12" pageNumber="561" refString="Yang, D. (1996 b) New species of Hercostomus and Ludovicius from North China (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Deutsche Entomologique Zeitschrift, 43 (2), 235 - 244. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 19960430207" type="journal article" year="1996" yearSuffix="b">
Yang 
<number box="[741,801,1665,1690]" pageId="12" pageNumber="561" value="1996.0">1996</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
